1
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:10,233
<i> Yes, Yolly.</i>

2
00:00:10,367 --> 00:00:11,367
<i> You're fired.</i>

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:15,133
<i>You can't just easily
kick me out of here.</i>

4
00:00:15,267 --> 00:00:17,667
<i> I know all your secrets.</i>

5
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:18,767
<i> Where is Mom?</i>

6
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:24,933
<i>My love for her
will never change.</i>

7
00:00:25,067 --> 00:00:26,367
<i> Even if you know the truth,</i>

8
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:30,400
<i>would you still accept her
knowing she deceived everyone?</i>

9
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:33,133
<i>If I find out that
you're still meeting her,</i>

10
00:00:33,267 --> 00:00:35,700
<i>just imagining it is
enough for me to know.</i>

11
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:37,667
<i>I will burn your reputation
so fast</i>

12
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:40,333
<i>that even your ashes will be
unrecognizable.</i>

13
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:43,133
<i>Do you enjoy ordering me around?</i>

14
00:00:43,267 --> 00:00:44,833
<i>I'm no longer afraid of you,
Greg.</i>

15
00:00:44,967 --> 00:00:48,433
<i>Your power over me has
officially expired.</i>

16
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:34,533
[CHUCKLES]

17
00:01:34,667 --> 00:01:37,500
[TENSE MUSIC]

18
00:01:37,633 --> 00:01:38,767
What else do you want?

19
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:44,267
For starters, I want a renewal
of vows for our marriage.

20
00:01:45,533 --> 00:01:48,033
I want you to invite
all of our friends

21
00:01:48,167 --> 00:01:50,967
and announce to them,
announce to the whole world,

22
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:53,700
that I am still the one you
choose.

23
00:01:53,833 --> 00:01:56,233
And if I don't agree to this?

24
00:01:56,367 --> 00:02:00,767
If you don't agree to this
and my other demands...

25
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:08,200
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

26
00:02:08,333 --> 00:02:11,833
I will personally destroy
your name.

27
00:02:13,167 --> 00:02:16,800
I will publicize all your dirt.

28
00:02:16,967 --> 00:02:19,167
Every single detail.

29
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:21,733
And it would be a huge scandal.

30
00:02:21,867 --> 00:02:25,467
And the one who loses
everything is you.

31
00:02:27,667 --> 00:02:30,100
You wouldn't want that, right?

32
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,000
Greg?

33
00:02:31,133 --> 00:02:41,033
[INTENSE MUSIC]

34
00:02:41,167 --> 00:02:51,133
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

35
00:03:11,633 --> 00:03:13,633
Marj?

36
00:03:13,767 --> 00:03:15,233
Marj.

37
00:03:15,367 --> 00:03:16,067
Coffee?

38
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,267
Thank you.

39
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:23,500
[DRAMATIC]

40
00:03:23,667 --> 00:03:25,933
Sorry about my wife's behavior
earlier.

41
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:27,433
She shouldn't have
escalated the issue.

42
00:03:29,633 --> 00:03:30,467
Hey.

43
00:03:32,267 --> 00:03:34,200
Why are you looking
at me like that?

44
00:03:35,567 --> 00:03:38,033
Why are you still kind to me?

45
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:41,800
Even though my mother did
something wrong.

46
00:03:43,567 --> 00:03:44,167
[SIGHS]

47
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:45,533
I know Dad.

48
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,967
I don't believe that Aunt Evelyn
initiated it.

49
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,100
He just took advantage

50
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,900
of your mother's vulnerability
and...

51
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:59,167
I believe that both our mothers
are victims here.

52
00:04:04,167 --> 00:04:09,133
[DRAMATIC]

53
00:04:09,267 --> 00:04:10,233
Thank you.

54
00:04:10,367 --> 00:04:13,567
I thought I no longer had
an ally in this house.

55
00:04:14,567 --> 00:04:15,467
Thank you.

56
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:23,467
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

57
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:29,600
[INTENSE]

58
00:04:29,767 --> 00:04:33,667
I'm so glad you're finally doing
what is right.

59
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:36,200
Stay away from your child.

60
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:37,867
You're a cancer to Marj.

61
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,767
No matter what you do,

62
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:42,733
you just break her heart
and destroy her.

63
00:04:45,567 --> 00:04:51,867
Regina, what can I do
so that you'll forgive me?

64
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:55,300
Forgive you?

65
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:56,500
Yolly?

66
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:57,933
Yes, Sir?

67
00:04:58,067 --> 00:05:02,033
How long have you been working
for us?

68
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,233
Oh my!

69
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:05,067
More than 30 years, Sir.

70
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,067
[CHUCKLES]

71
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:11,733
30 years.

72
00:05:11,867 --> 00:05:13,400
[CHUCKLES]

73
00:05:13,533 --> 00:05:17,333
In all that time,
you know me well, don't you?

74
00:05:17,467 --> 00:05:19,767
Yes, Sir.

75
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:22,533
In that case,

76
00:05:22,667 --> 00:05:30,200
you should know what I hate most
above all is being challenged.

77
00:05:31,033 --> 00:05:36,600
Just like what you did
when you reported me to Regina

78
00:05:36,767 --> 00:05:41,000
about what was happening
between me and Evelyn.

79
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:42,400
Oh, Sir.

80
00:05:42,533 --> 00:05:45,333
I'm sorry.

81
00:05:45,467 --> 00:05:47,700
Well...

82
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:52,433
I was only ordered
by Ma'am Regina

83
00:05:52,567 --> 00:05:55,567
to report all the actions
of Ma'am Evelyn.

84
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,533
I was caught in the middle, Sir.

85
00:05:57,667 --> 00:06:02,000
[LAUGHS]

86
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:06,400
[SIGHS]

87
00:06:06,533 --> 00:06:10,833
Forgiveness is a middle-class
concept, Evelyn.

88
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:14,133
And in my world,
we don't forgive.

89
00:06:14,267 --> 00:06:17,667
We simply write off
bad investments.

90
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,800
And you?

91
00:06:19,967 --> 00:06:21,967
You are a total loss.

92
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:26,367
Who pays your salary?

93
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:32,733
Who runs this house?

94
00:06:34,433 --> 00:06:38,933
Are you more afraid
of Regina than of me?

95
00:06:39,067 --> 00:06:43,233
Don't judge me for one mistake.

96
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:49,733
Please also remember the
good things I've done for you.

97
00:06:52,567 --> 00:06:57,367
Evelyn, do you hear
what you're saying?

98
00:06:58,867 --> 00:07:01,067
Just because you saved me
last time

99
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:03,033
doesn't mean I owe you forever.

100
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:09,467
Your heroic act hasn't earned
you a gold card to my sympathy.

101
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:12,900
Sir, I'm sorry.

102
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:21,033
I really had no intention
to betray you.

103
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:25,200
I swear, Sir.

104
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:28,733
[LAUGHS]

105
00:07:28,867 --> 00:07:31,733
But that's what you did, Yolly.

106
00:07:33,733 --> 00:07:37,467
This terrible mess
is all because of you.

107
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,633
Do you want me to call everyone?

108
00:07:42,533 --> 00:07:44,500
Tell them the truth.

109
00:07:44,633 --> 00:07:45,967
I don't care.

110
00:07:46,100 --> 00:07:52,233
Even if I take off this wig,
I am still Regina Torrecampo.

111
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:55,433
And they will all bow down
to me.

112
00:07:55,567 --> 00:07:58,567
And you, what are you?

113
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:00,700
You are an expired flavor
of the month

114
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:04,067
and you no longer belong
in this house.

115
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:06,367
It's that simple.

116
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:08,333
Pack all your things.

117
00:08:09,167 --> 00:08:14,833
Because I don't want you
working for us anymore.

118
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:18,067
Sir, please.

119
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:20,167
Yes, Yolly.

120
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:21,933
You're fired.

121
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,433
Sir, I'm sorry.

122
00:08:23,567 --> 00:08:25,133
Please have mercy.

123
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:27,300
Please don't throw me out.

124
00:08:31,967 --> 00:08:33,400
Stop begging, Yolly.

125
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,833
My decision won't change.

126
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:43,467
You don't even need
to kick me out.

127
00:08:45,767 --> 00:08:50,533
I will leave so Marj
won't be affected.

128
00:08:50,667 --> 00:08:52,000
Really?

129
00:08:52,133 --> 00:08:54,133
So, you really love your child.

130
00:08:55,133 --> 00:08:56,967
Good to know that you're leaving
here,

131
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:59,400
and you're staying away
from Marj.

132
00:08:59,533 --> 00:09:02,400
But you know, that's not enough.

133
00:09:02,533 --> 00:09:05,333
It's not enough to stay away
from her.

134
00:09:05,467 --> 00:09:08,800
It would be good if you
disappear from her life.

135
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:12,400
Entirely.

136
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:15,733
Sir, well...

137
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:22,333
You can't just suddenly
throw me out.

138
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:26,500
I know all your secrets.

139
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:33,533
I understand.

140
00:09:34,567 --> 00:09:37,533
Be angry with me
because I have a sin on you.

141
00:09:37,667 --> 00:09:40,767
But you don't need to be cruel.

142
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:46,400
You don't need to hit
someone just to feel better.

143
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:49,267
Sir.

144
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:50,733
Don't threaten me, Yolly.

145
00:09:50,867 --> 00:09:51,500
[COUGHING]

146
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:55,867
Like I said, you know me.

147
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:59,000
You knew what I'm capable of.

148
00:09:59,133 --> 00:10:01,100
You might regret this.

149
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:02,600
You will regret this!

150
00:10:02,733 --> 00:10:04,367
Sir, I'm really sorry.

151
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,733
Sir! Sir, I'm really sorry.

152
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:15,800
[COUGHING]

153
00:10:15,933 --> 00:10:25,900
[INTENSE MUSIC]

154
00:10:27,867 --> 00:10:31,100
Evelyn, Evelyn...

155
00:10:33,033 --> 00:10:36,500
Please don't give me unsolicited
advice.

156
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,733
I'm not being cruel, darling.

157
00:10:43,933 --> 00:10:46,567
I just want to clean my house
and get rid of the garbage.

158
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:50,533
So, if that's okay with you,
please hurry up

159
00:10:50,667 --> 00:10:54,467
because I plan to sanitize
my room the moment you leave.

160
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:59,200
[INTENSE MUSIC]

161
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:08,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

162
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:12,667
[SOBBING]

163
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:16,267
[INTENSE]

164
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:19,433
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

165
00:11:19,567 --> 00:11:22,467
[COUGHING]

166
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:23,533
Yolly?

167
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:26,700
Now, you may go.

168
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:29,933
Go!

169
00:11:30,067 --> 00:11:40,033
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

170
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:46,900
[INTENSE MUSIC]

171
00:11:55,833 --> 00:12:05,800
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

172
00:12:08,667 --> 00:12:10,300
Mom.

173
00:12:10,433 --> 00:12:12,267
Jobert is ready.

174
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:14,200
And Pong too.

175
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:19,433
Jobert, come here, my child.

176
00:12:23,667 --> 00:12:28,567
Jobert, there's no need.

177
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:32,833
Because only Mom is leaving.

178
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:39,333
Jobert will stay
with his sister.

179
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:44,533
Yes.

180
00:12:44,667 --> 00:12:45,767
Yes, my child.

181
00:12:49,567 --> 00:12:55,767
So, Jobert, listen to Mom.

182
00:12:57,967 --> 00:13:00,000
Be a good boy, okay.

183
00:13:00,133 --> 00:13:01,700
Be a good boy, Jobert.

184
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:12,633
And you'll be a good boy,
and a good uncle too.

185
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:18,033
You'll also be a good brother
to Marj.

186
00:13:18,167 --> 00:13:19,200
Okay?

187
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:21,433
Do you understand me?

188
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,433
Right? You understand me,
Jobert?

189
00:13:23,567 --> 00:13:24,700
You're a good boy.

190
00:13:25,667 --> 00:13:30,833
And you'll always defend
your sister

191
00:13:30,967 --> 00:13:34,600
when people mistreat her,
Jobert.

192
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:42,900
And also, you'll always follow

193
00:13:43,033 --> 00:13:48,267
everything your sister asks you
to do, okay?

194
00:13:53,733 --> 00:14:02,733
And always remember, Jobert,
Mom loves you very much.

195
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:05,700
Okay, Jobert?

196
00:14:07,567 --> 00:14:11,333
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

197
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:12,633
Hug me, Jobert.

198
00:14:12,767 --> 00:14:20,167
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

199
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:25,067
Why is Mom still leaving?

200
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:29,133
[SOBBING]

201
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:30,733
- Why?
- Mom is leaving

202
00:14:30,867 --> 00:14:34,000
because Mom has something

203
00:14:34,133 --> 00:14:38,000
she should have done
a long time ago.

204
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:42,867
Just be a good boy.

205
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,100
Be a good boy, okay?

206
00:14:46,667 --> 00:14:48,967
Go play with Pong for now, okay?

207
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:52,100
Pong will stay too.

208
00:14:52,233 --> 00:14:55,000
Pong and I will stay here.

209
00:14:55,133 --> 00:14:56,567
We're not leaving.

210
00:14:59,367 --> 00:15:01,233
That's right. Good boy.

211
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:04,567
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

212
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:06,300
I love you.

213
00:15:06,433 --> 00:15:07,267
That's a good boy.

214
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:17,367
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

215
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:30,167
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

216
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:06,700
Yes, it's a good thing I found
an apartment near the mansion.

217
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:08,867
At least I can visit them
anytime.

218
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,367
Hannah, I'll call you back,
okay?

219
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:13,333
Just a moment.

220
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:16,400
Jobert?

221
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:19,133
Jobert, what happened?

222
00:16:19,467 --> 00:16:20,567
Are you crying?

223
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:24,533
Where's Mom?

224
00:16:24,667 --> 00:16:25,667
[GASPS]

225
00:16:31,233 --> 00:16:34,100
<i> Marj, I'm sorry.</i>

226
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:35,767
<i> I changed my plan.</i>

227
00:16:36,067 --> 00:16:38,800
<i>I won't be moving
to the apartment you found.</i>

228
00:16:39,267 --> 00:16:41,867
<i>I need to go somewhere
farther away.</i>

229
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:44,933
<i>Somewhere I won't
be a burden to you.</i>

230
00:16:45,067 --> 00:16:46,733
<i> I love you and Jobert</i>

231
00:16:46,867 --> 00:16:50,867
<i>so I can't bear seeing you get
hurt because of me.</i>

232
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:54,067
<i>I don't want to be a burden
to you ever again.</i>

233
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:57,133
<i>I don't want to ruin your lives,
yours and Jobert's.</i>

234
00:16:57,367 --> 00:17:00,333
<i>So, it's better
for the two of you</i>

235
00:17:00,467 --> 00:17:02,467
<i>if I don't show myself for now.</i>

236
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,600
[SOBBING]

237
00:17:03,733 --> 00:17:06,033
<i> I'll go away for now</i>

238
00:17:06,167 --> 00:17:08,600
<i>so you'll be far
from the trouble I bring.</i>

239
00:17:08,733 --> 00:17:16,000
[SOBBING]

240
00:17:16,167 --> 00:17:19,600
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

241
00:17:19,733 --> 00:17:20,500
Weng!

242
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:21,767
Weng, where is Mom?

243
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:24,167
Ma'am, she already called
a taxi downstairs.

244
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:25,767
She took her luggage.

245
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:29,100
Mom!

246
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:32,733
Mom!

247
00:17:32,867 --> 00:17:36,933
[DRAMATIC]

248
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:38,033
Mom, wait!

249
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:38,967
Mom!

250
00:17:41,633 --> 00:17:42,433
Mom!

251
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:47,333
Mom!

252
00:17:47,467 --> 00:17:57,433
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

253
00:17:58,133 --> 00:18:00,700
I called our old apartment
where we used to live.

254
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:04,567
They said Mom didn't
pass by there.

255
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:07,367
Have you already
called her friends?

256
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:10,300
Well, most of her friends
are from Batangas.

257
00:18:10,433 --> 00:18:14,367
If she ends up there,
she'll probably arrive later.

258
00:18:14,500 --> 00:18:15,567
That makes sense.

259
00:18:16,867 --> 00:18:18,700
You know, this is my fault.

260
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:22,067
I made her feel like
she was a burden to me.

261
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:25,333
But that isn't true.

262
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:27,733
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

263
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:32,800
Whenever I get tired

264
00:18:32,933 --> 00:18:35,833
and struggle to take care of
Jasmine,

265
00:18:35,967 --> 00:18:38,667
she's the one who supports me.

266
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:42,300
Whenever I lose my courage

267
00:18:42,433 --> 00:18:44,600
because of the problems
between Paolo and me,

268
00:18:44,733 --> 00:18:46,500
she's the one
who gives me strength.

269
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:51,067
[SPEAKS IN VISAYAN LANGUAGE]

270
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:54,200
I'm sure your mom is safe.

271
00:18:54,333 --> 00:18:55,633
You should rest.

272
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,433
It's dangerous
if you get drained.

273
00:18:59,133 --> 00:19:00,633
You're right.

274
00:19:00,767 --> 00:19:03,333
My child needs me.

275
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:05,267
I can't abandon her.

276
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:07,667
That's why I need to be strong.

277
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,800
But honestly,

278
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,933
I was overwhelmed by everything
that happened.

279
00:19:16,633 --> 00:19:17,733
I don't know if...

280
00:19:19,233 --> 00:19:21,867
I don't know if I can
handle all of this.

281
00:19:24,433 --> 00:19:26,133
What? That's okay.

282
00:19:30,133 --> 00:19:32,967
She really didn't say goodbye
to anyone.

283
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:34,733
Not even to Ma'am Marj.

284
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:37,100
She just left.

285
00:19:37,233 --> 00:19:38,433
Good riddance.

286
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:42,633
Didn't she say
where she was going?

287
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:46,367
She didn't, Sir.

288
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:48,533
Ma'am Marj is already panicking.

289
00:19:49,733 --> 00:19:52,967
Let me know immediately
if there's any news about her.

290
00:19:53,933 --> 00:19:55,167
Yes, Sir.

291
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:58,000
Don't tell me you're still
worried about that woman.

292
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:01,633
- Go on.
- Yes, Sir.

293
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:10,967
Are you starting trouble again?

294
00:20:12,967 --> 00:20:15,300
Because you keep provoking me.

295
00:20:17,533 --> 00:20:19,000
And you know what,
because of that,

296
00:20:19,133 --> 00:20:23,833
I've decided to update the terms
and conditions of our marriage.

297
00:20:25,867 --> 00:20:28,367
Cut all communication
with that woman.

298
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:31,100
If I find out you're
still meeting her,

299
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:33,767
just imagining it is enough
for me to know.

300
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,633
I will burn your reputation
so fast

301
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:38,300
that even your ashes
will be unrecognizable.

302
00:20:42,533 --> 00:20:44,633
Do you enjoy ordering me around?

303
00:20:48,267 --> 00:20:51,400
Is that the best your fragile
ego can do, Greg?

304
00:20:52,233 --> 00:20:55,433
Go ahead, hit me until I break,

305
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:58,667
so I can add assault to my
colorful list of reasons

306
00:20:58,800 --> 00:20:59,767
to destroy you.

307
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:09,100
[INTENSE MUSIC]

308
00:21:09,267 --> 00:21:11,033
I'm no longer afraid of you,
Greg.

309
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:15,700
Just like my patience,

310
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:19,800
your power over me has
officially expired.

311
00:21:19,933 --> 00:21:22,833
You spent years trying
to break me.

312
00:21:24,733 --> 00:21:26,733
But you've only managed
to turn me

313
00:21:26,867 --> 00:21:29,067
into something unbreakable.

314
00:21:31,767 --> 00:21:33,967
So welcome to my world, Greg.

315
00:21:35,767 --> 00:21:39,367
Welcome to my world of pain.

316
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:49,467
[INTENSE MUSIC]

317
00:22:01,933 --> 00:22:06,600
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

318
00:22:06,733 --> 00:22:09,333
[MARJ SOBS]

319
00:22:09,467 --> 00:22:12,067
What's the matter?

320
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:15,600
You know that Mother Evelyn
was going to leave, right?

321
00:22:16,433 --> 00:22:20,833
But we never talked about
her leaving on her own

322
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:24,067
and not telling me
where she was going.

323
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:32,367
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

324
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:35,967
You know,

325
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:39,300
the fights between Mom and me
are just like ours.

326
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:42,267
We fight and make up.

327
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:47,167
But no matter how much we argue,

328
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:50,500
my love for her
will never change.

329
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:57,867
Even if...

330
00:23:00,133 --> 00:23:01,467
Even if you already
know the truth?

331
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:05,633
Even if her mistake is
bigger than you expected?

332
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:08,867
Would you still accept her

333
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,500
even knowing she deceived
all of you?

334
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,167
Yes.

335
00:23:17,067 --> 00:23:21,433
When you love someone,
you don't judge them,

336
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:25,700
you don't push them away,
and you don't give up on them.

337
00:23:26,933 --> 00:23:30,233
I wish that during the time
when Mom was at her weakest

338
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:32,867
and struggling
against temptation,

339
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:35,200
she had come to me

340
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:39,100
so I could help her be strong
and not make that mistake.

341
00:23:40,933 --> 00:23:47,700
That's why honesty and
communication are so important.

342
00:23:48,733 --> 00:23:51,333
Love, I'm sorry.

343
00:23:51,467 --> 00:23:54,667
I didn't tell you right away
about Mom and Dad.

344
00:23:56,667 --> 00:23:57,867
Forget about that.

345
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,167
It's over.

346
00:24:01,800 --> 00:24:05,300
I promise, from now on,
I won't hide anything from you.

347
00:24:06,233 --> 00:24:08,167
I'll tell you everything.

348
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:12,267
Okay.

349
00:24:14,267 --> 00:24:17,033
Just focus on taking care
of Jasmine, okay?

350
00:24:17,167 --> 00:24:20,333
I'll take care of finding
Mother Evelyn.

351
00:24:20,467 --> 00:24:23,500
I'll call all my contacts
in the police force.

352
00:24:23,633 --> 00:24:26,567
Maybe they can help us
find Mother Evelyn.

353
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,600
Thank you.

354
00:24:31,533 --> 00:24:41,500
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

355
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:43,833
Hello?

356
00:24:43,967 --> 00:24:44,867
Hello.

357
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:47,300
Yes, can you hear me?

358
00:24:47,433 --> 00:24:50,700
Yes, this is Marj,
Evelyn's daughter.

359
00:24:50,833 --> 00:24:53,867
Okay, please call or text me

360
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,667
if my mom happens to pass by
there.

361
00:24:57,033 --> 00:24:58,000
Thank you.

362
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:04,433
You know what, Marj?

363
00:25:04,567 --> 00:25:08,167
Chasing after someone who
clearly doesn't want to be found

364
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:09,933
is so exhausting.

365
00:25:10,067 --> 00:25:11,767
It really wears you down.

366
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:12,633
Look at your skin.

367
00:25:12,767 --> 00:25:14,033
It's already so dry.

368
00:25:14,167 --> 00:25:16,533
You're literally rotting
from stress.

369
00:25:18,633 --> 00:25:21,433
You know, if I were you,
I would stop this already.

370
00:25:21,567 --> 00:25:22,700
Let her go.

371
00:25:22,833 --> 00:25:25,100
Anyway, she chose to leave.

372
00:25:25,233 --> 00:25:28,300
Maybe she realized that
she was also a burden to you.

373
00:25:31,267 --> 00:25:37,933
If you want us to get along,
Marj, forget about her.

374
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:39,467
You don't need her.

375
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,233
I'm here anyway.

376
00:25:41,367 --> 00:25:43,767
And I can be a good
mother-in-law to you

377
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:45,967
if you do everything
I tell you to do.

378
00:25:46,100 --> 00:25:48,433
[INTENSE MUSIC]

379
00:25:49,067 --> 00:25:51,700
Mom, I want us to be okay,

380
00:25:51,833 --> 00:25:54,200
and I am willing to follow
everything you want.

381
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:56,900
Except for one thing.

382
00:25:58,267 --> 00:26:00,433
I will not forget my mother.

383
00:26:01,633 --> 00:26:03,533
I love her,

384
00:26:03,667 --> 00:26:06,433
and I will not replace her
with anyone else.

385
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:09,867
Okay, fine.

386
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:11,967
If that's how you want it.

387
00:26:12,100 --> 00:26:13,900
If you want to fool yourself

388
00:26:14,033 --> 00:26:15,433
into believing your mother
is kind.

389
00:26:16,533 --> 00:26:18,067
Actually, that's fine too.

390
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:22,100
Because watching you stress
gives me so much satisfaction.

391
00:26:23,033 --> 00:26:24,933
Because while you suffer,

392
00:26:25,067 --> 00:26:27,000
Evelyn can't do anything
about it.

393
00:26:27,133 --> 00:26:28,833
It feels like I've gotten
my revenge.

394
00:26:31,467 --> 00:26:41,433
[INTENSE MUSIC]

395
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:45,533
Love, are you okay?

396
00:26:45,667 --> 00:26:47,000
I'm just going home.

397
00:26:47,133 --> 00:26:49,167
I have something important
I need to take care of.

398
00:26:49,300 --> 00:26:52,433
Something that I should have
taken care of a long time ago.

399
00:26:52,567 --> 00:26:55,067
Don't you enjoy
being together with me?

400
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:56,333
Let's just finish this!

401
00:26:56,467 --> 00:26:58,633
Just grant me my final request.

402
00:26:58,767 --> 00:26:59,833
Let's do it.

403
00:26:59,967 --> 00:27:01,500
One last sex.

404
00:27:01,633 --> 00:27:05,267
An angry, sweaty, hard bang,
Paolo!

405
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,867
Kuya Bait!

406
00:27:08,667 --> 00:27:09,500
Jobert?

407
00:27:11,133 --> 00:27:11,833
Before we start blaming
each other,

408
00:27:11,967 --> 00:27:12,900
let's check on Jobert first.

409
00:27:13,033 --> 00:27:14,200
It looks like he recorded us.

410
00:27:14,333 --> 00:27:15,900
Give me your phone!

411
00:27:16,067 --> 00:27:16,867
[THUDS]

412
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:20,700
[INTENSE MUSIC]
